    {
      "id": "lv7v4rl6",
      "questionNumber": 3,
      "questionText": "<p>For the Compounds :</p>\n<p>(A) $$\\mathrm{H}_3 \\mathrm{C}-\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{O}-\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{CH}_3$$</p>\n<p>(B) $$\\mathrm{H}_3 \\mathrm{C}-\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{CH}_3$$</p>\n<p>(C) <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lv7omk9n/3ae491e7-67c8-44be-9e82-08f2fc6ff955/1dce9eb0-feda-11ee-af99-a751fb126769/file-1lv7omk9o.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lv7omk9n/3ae491e7-67c8-44be-9e82-08f2fc6ff955/1dce9eb0-feda-11ee-af99-a751fb126769/file-1lv7omk9o.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2024 (Online) 5th April Morning Shift Chemistry - Alcohols, Phenols and Ethers Question 27 English 1\"></p>\n<p>(D) <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lv7olzvt/4f13f5d8-6711-4ee3-905c-453b38b404ac/0e0f8d90-feda-11ee-af99-a751fb126769/file-1lv7olzvu.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lv7olzvt/4f13f5d8-6711-4ee3-905c-453b38b404ac/0e0f8d90-feda-11ee-af99-a751fb126769/file-1lv7olzvu.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2024 (Online) 5th April Morning Shift Chemistry - Alcohols, Phenols and Ethers Question 27 English 2\"></p>\n<p>The increasing order of boiling point is :</p>\n<p>Choose the correct answer from the options given below :</p>",
      "options": [
        "$$\n(\\mathrm{D})<(\\mathrm{C})<(\\mathrm{A})<(\\mathrm{B})\n$$",
        "$$\n(\\mathrm{B})<(\\mathrm{A})<(\\mathrm{C})<(\\mathrm{D})\n$$",
        "$$\n(\\mathrm{A})<(\\mathrm{B})<(\\mathrm{C})<(\\mathrm{D})\n$$",
        "$$\\mathrm{\n(B)<(A)<(D)<(C)}$$"
